				<td colspan="2"><span>Because thats what those people want. They don't care about playing the game, they are after &quot;phat lewts&quot; and will scream and bitch until the devs pave a yellow brick road to &quot;phat lewt&quot; city so they can hook arms and jog on over without so much as a bead of sweat singing joy joy songs. They don't care or want to learn how to play a bard, thats not the point, they just chose bard as a vessel on which to lavish loot. And seeing that the end game isn't getting any easier they whine and bitch about things most serious bards have stopped thinking about.
<br />

<br />
Bugs are important, things that are broken are important, poor fore-sight on the part of devs are important. When things do not work the way the developers intended that is something to moan and bitch about, not things you &quot;wish&quot; would happen. Continuing to bitch about things you &quot;wish&quot; only clutters the things that are genuinely of issue.
<br />

