				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: WHY!?~<a name="53140"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 10:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Instead of whining and moaning about autotwisting, we should be trying to get port songs, FD, group bind and group gate (with yes/no boxes!) songs, and a pet!
<br />

<br />
And maybe raise some caps like our charm cap.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and increase melee dps.  I want to give rogues a run for their money!
<br />

<br />
Oh, and give us some half - decent nukes, too!  I want to crit for 3k every 3 seconds!
<br />

<br />
Oh, and give us a better slow.  I'm thinking 65% isn't too much to ask for.
<br />

<br />
And let clarity and the other mana regen effect us!  We're mana classes now, too!
<br />

<br />
Hmm, while we're at it, we should get our hps increased.  And our damage mitigation.
<br />

<br />
Oh, oh, make our lull unresistable like monk's!
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hmm, come to think of it, why can't I use 2H weapons?  I don't think it's unreasonable for a bard to go into a fight swinging a 2 handed sword or whatever.  And archery?  We're jack of all trades, right?
<br />

<br />
Oh, and let us change into frogloks if we want permanently.  Michigan frog, any one?  Actually, just make all races bard usable.  The dwarven armies in other lore had drummers, and the ogres and trolls had crude horns, and the halflings had the occasional bard..
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Come on people, we don't need any thing more.  Some nice AE mez's, and most of the stuff outlined in that first comment would absolutely ROCK, but all-in-all we don't need any thing else.  All the time, as long as you play the class right, other classes will talk about envying you.  Is there a reason for this?   Yes.  Bards are more skill based then any other class, which is why they should be allowed to be over powered.  SKILL-BASED.  That means instead of needing to go to time to be an above average bard (unlike tanks, or dps classes, or..) a bard in lvl 10 newbie gear can be superb.
<br />

<br />
How many classes can go and do a hard LDoN NAKED?  Maybe a monk, maybe a... well... actually, no, just bards and monks.  And monks will be severely hampered.  But bards can do it butt naked and the only thing stopping him is skill (would take a lot of carefullness to deal with your suddenly low mana regen and pool) and his dps is usually pretty low anyways so taking it out won't do too much.  I have made pulls naked before from turning down the wrong way and having a corpse hidden away from me by a bunch of see invis mobs before (ok once), and it's doable.
<br />

<br />
What does all that mean?  Stop your whining and learn to play a bard.  Oh, and give us FD and a pet.   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
