				<td colspan="2"><span>Razs your post is weird because it has nothing to do with the topic of the thread.
<br />

<br />
The thing is, and I know lanolar is spreading this out over a lot of threads too, although it seems like every thread turns into this...we do need something more.  I know not everybody raids, but definitely there is a lacking role in the raid game.  I mean, I even see it in elemental planes stage of the game.  
<br />

<br />
I wanna play the fun list-the-overpowered-things game too!
<br />

<br />
Raise charm cap overpowered? In xp groups obviously, but how about a little diversity like a dire charm type song.  DC pets aren't a whole lot of dps and it would help out when such mobs are available.
<br />

<br />
Increase melee dps overpowered?  Hardly.  It'd be a really small advantage overall, because I would still rather see other abilities be more useful than melee, but it definitely wouldn't hurt.  As it is, I really don't even bother to swing on raids because my 75 dps isn't worth the effort of following a mob around in a circle.
<br />

<br />
How about instead of 3 second nukes we get like a 5 second cast time 120dd base nuke?  I mean, it's not like you could be twisting through that, so you're neglecting your group to put out more dps, but again on a raid, dps is all we can really hope to offer.  And at 120 base, the most you can hope for non-crit would be about 500....500dd in 5 seconds is what 100dps?  So we could push maybe 200ish dps which would almost put us on par with a ranger for dps.  Think now, we're sacrificing everything else for raw dps, so it's not really overpowered, it's diversity of the class.  So in theory you could have many bards like how you can have many rangers, and they wouldn't have to step on feet by wasting DoT space on mobs or overwriting each others' dots for dps.
<br />

<br />
Give us a better slow?  Why?  During raids the only slow bards would possibly do is a pre-slow during a pull, and that gets resisted plenty.  During xp groups if you really need 15% more slow then what you probably need instead is a different tank.
<br />

<br />
Who needs more mana regen?  The only time I'm out of mana is fresh from a rez, in which instance it would be nice if mana regen effects worked on me, <b>how about my own songs?</b>  Especially on raids it's kinda hard to get back into the pull action if I can't fade to split...I'm severely handicapped.  I still go out and do it because I don't want someone else to take over my job, I just either have to be a lot more careful or oops big train inc.  Either way my raid is still happy with my pulling because of the pace I set, they don't mind a couple extra mobs in camp.
<br />

<br />
Unresistable lull like a monk's?  That'd be tight.  In fact, how about we get one, and it work independently of our current one and be on a 18 second timer like a monk's?  Would sure make ldon hard a lot easier for a bard and maybe, just maybe, I could get a group there over a monk.  It's retarded to think that monks deserve such a leg up over a bard just because they got shafted for so long.  Put me on an even playing field and I won't whine about it.  Monks needed something and they got it, but bards were shafted indirectly because of it.
<br />

<br />
Ok, now I want to respond to the original post of the thread, about autotwist ruining our class.  There's nothing stopping a raiding guild from using bard bots as it stands.  1 play ae chorus the whole time, 1 play ae resists the whole time.  They don't even have to be part of the raid!  In fact, you could have 2 bard bots out of raid, and then throw in a bot in a dps class or 2 that just plays echo of the trusik!  It's silly to think that just because a class is bot-able a raid would replace its real players of that class with bots.  h*ll, I can box a cleric in rotation but my guild won't let me unless we're that short on clerics.  They would rather have someone fully devoted to the rotation, and I don't blame them.  And likewise, they would rather have a fulltime bard than a stupid bot.
<br />

<br />
The upside to autotwist would be a reduced chance for carpal tunnel syndrome maybe...and how about the ability to talk to my friends while I play instead of having to type in 2.5 second lines or else map my hotkeys to f keys so I can type while I twist.  Probably the only downside to autotwist would be the surge of unskilled bards popping up, but just like any other class, if they aren't very good, they won't get many groups or whatever.
<br />

<br />
I already have a niche carved out for myself.  If 100 unskilled bard bots hit 65 tomorrow, I would still be able to get groups with the people I want to play with.  I am beyond the &quot;crappy bards make me look bad&quot; phase.  People will notice you for your skill, just as they notice a good warrior for his skill in getting and holding aggro etc.
<br />

<br />
I would be in favor of an autotwist, it's a convenience factor.  I can keep 3 songs up with absolutely no effort, however I can't make a macro to do it for me so I have to keep manually twisting over and over till the day's end.  It isn't a measure of my skill at this point, it maybe was when I was level 20 and still learning the class...but definitely not anymore.
<br />

<br />
Sorry for how long the post is, but I think I covered just about everything~</span></td>
