				<td colspan="2"><span>Auto - Twist? no thanks - dumb idea
<br />

<br />
Twisting is what makes a bard a bard. It's what defines us as a class on the player end. 
<br />

<br />
I hate seeing people that use macros, or bot-programs in the game. If there were a way to detect it, I personally think every single one of them should have their accounts banned, permently.
<br />

<br />
If you don't want to twist, don't play a bard. If you want the unending abilities a bard has (because of spells that cost NO mana, and can be cast WHILE moving) you have to give something up. In a bards case - long duration spells is what we give up. Meaning, we have to keep casting over and over. If you could push 1 button and &quot;auto-twist&quot; you have now taken away that detriment entirely. If you can have MULTIPLE effects up almost indefinitely from pushing 1 button the &quot;balance&quot; to songs NOT costing mana is completely lost.
<br />

<br />
Bards don't have &quot;spells&quot;, they have SONGS. If you want to use your voice or insturments to fill peoples arms with strength or speed, to heal their wounds, or to confuse a mob, you have to keep singing. When the song goes- the effects. Consider Alt+ 11,22,33,44,55,11,22,33,44,55...... akin to playing your insturments while you weave 5 songs together into a cresendo of inspiring power. It makes perfect sence to me, and NOT twisting them seems nothig more than LAZY in my eyes. 
<br />

<br />
Twisting has been a fact of life for a bard since day one. It part of the class. In fact, its a defining charactistic of the class. Changing it damages the integrity of the class. Consider it the &quot;cost&quot; of being able to do all that you CAN do. </span></td>
