				<td colspan="2"><span>You can still tell the difference between a good bard and a dink bard any day of the week.  Twisting doesn't show anything more than you're not a piece of total crap as it is now.  There's still our pulling, or our CC, or any number of other things that bards can do.  Even if some do have complaints about pulling not being up to par in some places, get over it.  I'd like to see a monk keep 5 mobs mezzed.  Moving on... on the flip side, if you're not pulling and you have absolutely no need to be CC, you're not going to shine all that much.  Tell me how this is any different than what you do on a raid or in a group if you're just sitting and playing songs without an autotwist?  Oh yeah, that's right.  With an autotwist you can at least be sociable.  Whereas before you would sit there, not having much affect on the outcome of things, and it seems like you're in your own little world doing whatever.
