				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: WHY!?~<a name="53871"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 27 04 12:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For the guy that said my post was weird because it had nothing to do with the topic, well, it did.
<br />

<br />
The point is that bards are really, really powerful.  Maybe at the end game it doesn't shine as much, but who can get to the end game without a bard in the first place?
<br />

<br />
Everything I stated is something that's been whined for by bards.  The thing I was trying to point out is that these requests are ridiculous.  Maybe one on one the things wouldn't be so over powered, but all together?  Imagine pumping out 1k dps if you get a crit while slowing something for 65% and making infallible single pulls as your new pet runs about smacking stuff up.
<br />

<br />
Would we be over powered?  Yeah.
<br />
Would other classes whine and complain?  Yeah.
<br />
Would said other classes thus get new toys to compensate?  Yeah.
<br />
Would bards be back to where they started?  Yeah.
<br />
Would we whine for something else?  Yeah.
<br />
Would the cycle continue to repeat?  Yeah.
<br />
And it always has been.  Look at the content out there now - mobs that rampage for 5k, and they're yard trash.  If we continue to drive the content level up as we are doing now, the casual or non-uber players will just get ticked off and leave.  That leaves a very small percentage of people - the heavy raiders.  And ya know what?  They can't pay for all that it takes for SoE to keep running.  Jacked up prices (it's already happened!), half-finished expansions (/cough), and more and more publicity stunts.
<br />

<br />
EQ is dying and no one seems to realise it.  It's not going to be quick and right away, its infrastructure is decaying slowly.
<br />

<br />
How soon can we expect trash mobs that ae rampage for 10k?  Not that far off, I imagine.
<br />

<br />
Then, pitted against the average Joes who have tanks with 8k hp on a good day... anything that's not instanced will be unattainable.  More reasons for the people who can't submit enough time to raid.
<br />

<br />
There are many reasons why people can't raid either, none of that 'You're not there because you don't want to be' hogwash.  I, for example, have had my computer stop being able to run EQ.  I now play on some one else's - and they come home and want their computer.  Sporadic and unreliable play times.  How am I supposed to look attractive to a raiding guild?  There are better equipped and equally (if not more so) skilled bards then me who ARE reliable time-wise and WILL do what they want, when they want it.
<br />

<br />
Basically, autotwisting is just another sign of the incoming death of EQ.  I am adamantly against it because any and all bones like this WILL contribute to this, one step at a time.
<br />

<br />
Or, you can ignore all that if you want.  
<br />

<br />
Also, I would be bored if I could autotwist.  Playing alts, I always find myself looking for something else to do.  As my SK, I find myself pulling, tanking, and what-not as I scrounge around hitting every button I can (I wear a shield just so I can spam bash).  I use the lowest level spells I can so that I can cast more.  I keep my pet up at all times (even when pulling a la pet splits or FD splits) just so I can have something else to do (pet attack, pet back off, etc.).
<br />

<br />
I will say this, though.  I doubt I think the same as every body else, and I am attracted to the bard class for reasons unlike every one else.
<br />

<br />
-I made a bard because my first char (a rogue) could never get groups.  It was originally just to solo.
<br />
-I found kiting boring.  I got a group.
<br />
-I loved the group.
<br />
-I continued to group.
<br />
-I stopped kiting.
<br />
-I now fill as many roles as I can as the bard while grouped, for the sole purpose of keeping myself busy.  I need to do something, else I get bored fast.  (I tried a shammy, I tried a wizzy, I tried a necro, I still have a bunch of other class alts and I find them all boring because of how often they're sitting around).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
