			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: WHY!?~<a name="53893"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 27 04 3:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I would be bored if I could autotwist.</span></blockquote>
<br />
If you could autotwist? Or if you <b>had</b> to autotwist?  There's a difference here.  If it were implemented, I could almost guarantee it would be optional, because so many people are obviously against it.  How could you be bored by it if you chose not to use the feature?
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The point is that bards are really, really powerful. Maybe at the end game it doesn't shine as much, but who can get to the end game without a bard in the first place?</span></blockquote>
<br />
Remember when everyone was saying &quot;who could get to elemental planes without vexthall gear?&quot;?  It can and has been done.  Guilds that have an average of 0-2 bards succeed just as much as guilds that have 5.
<br />

<br />
The point is <b>not</b> that bards are really, really powerful.  How powerful am I for being able to twist 3 songs together, which is what any joe shmoe bard should be able to do?  If the answer is less than &quot;really really powerful&quot;, then automating that annoyance would change nothing.  It's not like i'm asking to be able to automatically twist 8 songs at once, just 3, which is what I can do now more or less effortlessly, but I still have to give it my full attention because of timing (both game mechanics and lag issues).
<br />

<br />
What I really want auto-twist for is the ability to experience the game itsself, and to be able to talk to my friends while doing it.  When you group, how often do you look up from your casting bar?  How often do you type out complete thoughts?  How often do you feel even remotely relaxed?  Now take a look at the other people in your group.  If you have an enchanter, and they are not charming something, they're probably typing their hands off, which comes off as annoying to me because of all the stress I have from keeping my twist going.  I should be enjoying their conversation, but I can't, as every time I try to input, it's like:
<br />
Yeah I total32ly3242SHIT *shift-down &amp; enter*
<br />

<br />
If there was a key to twist 3 songs at once, I could map it to an f-key or the numpad, and my conversation would be much more possible.  I could stop in the middle of my sentence, leisurely hit the twist key to keep my songs going, and continue with my thought.
<br />

<br />
I am tired of standing around in plane of knowledge all day instead of grouping, because I would rather relax and chat up a couple of my close friends instead of grind xp that I don't really need anymore, and be stressed out doing it.  If I could auto-twist, I could actually group and enjoy myself all at the same time, and I wouldn't feel so nit-picky about little things that happen during grouping.
<br />

<br />
Seriously, good bards are very grouchy these days, and I would put money on the fact that it's because we have to micromanage our class and so we become overattentive of small things that happen around us.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I tried a shammy, I tried a wizzy, I tried a necro, I still have a bunch of other class alts and I find them all boring because of how often they're sitting around</span></blockquote>
<br />
Maybe I'm just weird.  I find med breaks to be a relaxing time.  Perhaps it's because I prefer chatting to fighting, but it definitely gives me a chance to collect my thoughts, no pun intended.  And when we sit around before raids while we form up, I use that time to read message boards or catch up with friends.  Or while I'm medding up when I play a twink I can take the med break time to look up items I might want to get for said twink on allakhazam or something.
<br />

<br />
Twisting as a bard keeps me so occupied I can't do anything else attentively.  I hate being in an xp group for more than about 30 minutes because I lose interest, especially since most xp groups stop talking after about 15 minutes, and then it's a mindless grind.
<br />

<br />
I think a real issue is this.  For most classes, as they get better gear and/or become more skilled, they don't have to be quite so active in playing their class.  Take warriors for instance.  A warrior with subpar aggro weapons is gonna be working his butt off to maintain aggro, kicking and taunting endlessly.  A warrior with a BoW can pretty much turn on autoattack and maintain aggro throughout a fight, unless someone is trying purposely to take aggro from him.  
<br />
For me, even when I slum in lower planes (bot, pov, poi, whatever) it's always the same 3 keys over and over again every 3 seconds.  It doesn't matter how easy the mobs are, I will always have to do that, because that's the way my class works.  And I have to do it in a well-timed manner.  A wizard in lower planes with Strike of Solusek can cast once per fight and be as effective as a lower level wizard casting 3-4 times.
<br />
For me?  3 keys at a 3 second interval between each one, from now until forever.
<br />

<br />
It's silly to argue against adding an option to gameplay if it's.....optional?  On the EQLive boards I posted an analogy for auto-twisting being akin to cruise control in a car.  Sure, I can maintain a speed manually if I want to.  But why would I when I can use cruise control and I can sit back and have driving be a relaxing time.  I still am paying attention to steering, so there's still something there that I'm doing, but the annoyance of manually keeping my speed constant is gone.  This is incredibly similar to what auto-twist would do for me, the difference is, I can put a cruise control in my car if I want.  I can't put auto-twist on my bard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
