				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: WHY!?~<a name="54252"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 29 04 10:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The only argument I see as valid against auto-twisting is bot bards. Bards have limited roles to fill in raids, if you can get a bard to auto-twist damage focus and another to auto-twist mana/resists, then get another to auto-twist a MA song set, why have a person behind bards at all? Just make a bard bot, PL to 65, get them the songs you need, then make a /autofollow hotkey. Boom, your very own mana/resist/haste/focus/AC/Cha bard bot, and you know what, I bet an auto-twisting bard bot could keep songs up much more reliably than some stinky human behind a keyboard.
<br />

<br />
Certainly, many of you don't care about the raiding side of EQ. You just want to have fun in one group settings, which is perfectly fine. But when you propose a change that is detrimental to a part of the bard population, you have to be a little empathetic to your fellow bards and say, hang on, this may not be the best idea for everyone.
<br />

<br />
You make an argument saying the older bards don't want change. Well, sometimes it takes the older bards and their experiences to see where the changes that are being made are going to cause problems down the road that the lesser experienced bards do not see right now.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
